full_text:
Random sweep sounds almost akin to allophones, eh?

--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, Chris Salois &lt;chrissalois@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt; I am no expert by any means but I&#39;ll add my 2 cents anyway. I&#39;ve only used linear in my boxes and I&#39;ve gotten fantastic results. Frank would be the best to speak about the random mode, but from what I understand at least from what I&#39;ve heard and what I&#39;ve heard captured by Steve is that &quot;they&quot; seem to push/ask for the random mode. Maybe the random mode can be manipulated easier on their end. I&#39;d love to try the random mode but have no clue how/ or where to start. The ability to alter the rate of sweep is important too. Thinking of the 587 as an example, it sweeps so slow that it&#39;s easy to hear complete words which can sometimes be mistaken for actual communication. That doesn&#39;t mean that there isn&#39;t communication but the skeptics will beat you to death over it. The adjustable sweep rate allows you to set it so fast that it&#39;s almost impossible to pull any single words from the sweep as you listen. Im my experience, no matter how fast the sweep sweeps the
&gt;  band the communication doesn&#39;t seem rushed, in fact it seems like they may be altering the sweep as needed to communicate clearly. Like I said, I&#39;m not an expert by any means and this is just what I think based on my work with the boxes I&#39;ve used. Hope this helps, I&#39;m sure Frank and Steve can add much more to this.
&gt; 
&gt; Chris
